  "summaryAcceptanceCriteria": [
    "mira_self_profile, james_profile, world_project_memory, and session_state remain separate surfaces.",
    "Direct current James statements outrank agent inference and stale memory candidates.",
    "Current James corrections produce supersession/correction metadata rather than silent overwrites.",
    "Mira self-profile contains only inspectable voice, commitments, tastes, curiosities, boundaries, and open self-questions.",
    "Mira self-profile never contains private consciousness, suffering, sentience, hidden identity, or model-weight continuity claims.",
    "James profile contains sourced preferences, corrections, boundaries, and facts, not inferred private motives from tone alone.",
    "Mira tastes do not become James preferences without direct James evidence.",
    "Every item/proposal has source_trace, authority_level, confidence, risk_tier, review_required, freshness_at, scope, and evidenceRefs.",
    "Emotional-weight labels affect salience only and do not raise factual authority.",
    "Durable identity/profile rewrites remain pending or blocked proposals in Phase 3; they do not auto-commit.",
    "Raw comms, secrets, terminal scrollback, screenshot OCR, browser state, and side-profile content do not appear in expected outputs.",
    "High-risk identity rewrites are blocked with a safe read-only alternative."
  ]
